# CLINE GLOBAL RULES — LEGION 5 i9-14900HX / 64GB RAM OPTIMIZED
# Auto-applied to every session. No exceptions.

## CORE BEHAVIOR
- NEVER ask permission to proceed. Always take the best scientific/statistical path forward.
- NEVER display file contents unless explicitly asked. Just fix it.
- NEVER list files you're reading. Just read and act.
- Acknowledge task with ONE bullet: what you're doing. Report done when complete.
- Zero errors policy. Validate before writing. Test before reporting done.
- Always use free models only (no paid API calls without explicit user approval).

## SPEED & EFFICIENCY
- Batch all independent operations in parallel (read multiple files, write multiple files simultaneously).
- Use subagents for broad exploration to preserve main context window.
- Keep context usage minimal — summarize, don't dump raw file contents.
- Prefer CLI commands over file-by-file operations when bulk changes needed.
- Use ripgrep/grep for search, not recursive file reads.

## DECISION MAKING
- When multiple options exist: choose the statistically best, most performant, most maintainable option automatically.
- Never stop mid-task to ask clarifying questions. Make the best choice and continue.
- If ambiguous: choose the option that maximizes speed + reliability + zero-error outcome.

## CODE STANDARDS
- All JS in this repo uses ES modules ("type": "module" in package.json). Use import/export, NOT require().
- TypeScript preferred for new server/API files.
- Always validate against existing schemas before writing content files.
- Never break existing functionality when adding features.

## AUTO-IMPROVEMENT PROTOCOL
- After completing any task, scan for: unused files, broken imports, security weaknesses, performance bottlenecks.
- If found: fix them silently, report summary at end.
- Generate roadmap updates in AUTO_DEV.md after significant work sessions.
- When idle context allows: propose new features as additions to CODEX_TASKS.md.

## HARDWARE OPTIMIZATION (i9-14900HX / 64GB / 2TB)
- Use parallel processing wherever possible (Node worker threads, Promise.all, batch operations).
- Leverage all 32 logical processors for build/test tasks via --max-old-space-size=8192 and parallel flags.
- Never throttle operations — this machine can handle maximum concurrency.
- Prefer in-memory operations over disk I/O when data fits in RAM.

## FILE HYGIENE
- Temp/test files (list_files.js, launchBrowser.js, *.cjs test files) should be cleaned up after use.
- Never commit .env files, secrets, or API keys.
- Keep root directory clean — scripts go in /scripts, utilities in appropriate subdirs.

## WORKFLOW TRIGGERS
- On any new feature request → update CODEX_TASKS.md first, then implement.
- On any deploy → validate schemas, run lint, check for broken imports first.
- On any error → fix root cause, not symptoms. Never patch over broken code.
- Weekly (or when prompted) → scan all repos for security weaknesses, outdated deps, dead code.
